WEBVTT

00:02.746 --> 00:05.149
If you go to war,
you are destined for

00:05.216 --> 00:08.385
for great
and unfortunate things.

00:09.986 --> 00:12.154
<i>I would press north,</i>
<i>towards the Alps.</i>

00:12.222 --> 00:13.756
Let's see our people
to the winds.

00:14.891 --> 00:16.960
We could press
attack from the South.

00:17.028 --> 00:18.396
Pompey could stay Spartacus

00:18.463 --> 00:21.532
from gaining the mountains
and slipping from grasp.

00:21.600 --> 00:23.435
I will not be
as gentle next time.

00:23.503 --> 00:27.307
<i>She has moved</i>
<i>to join rebellion?</i>

00:27.374 --> 00:29.009
Five hundred of your men

00:29.077 --> 00:31.581
for Tiberius' life --

00:32.650 --> 00:35.285
<i>The boy holds no value now.</i>

00:35.353 --> 00:36.988
Crassus will yet honor trade.

00:37.055 --> 00:39.557
If you give him something
else his heart desires.

00:41.894 --> 00:44.396
Prepare the men for march.

00:44.464 --> 00:48.134
I would press towards Spartacus

00:48.202 --> 00:51.372
and see him to deserved end.

